25:06.195 --> 25:08.663
<i>♪ Nights out ran me ragged ♪</i>

25:08.665 --> 25:12.700
<i>♪ Got tired of bein' nice
Out of habit ♪</i>

25:12.702 --> 25:14.769
<i>♪ You can ask
You can't have it ♪</i>

25:14.771 --> 25:18.272
<i>♪ Shorty back home
Snack wrapped in a blanket ♪</i>

25:18.274 --> 25:19.472
No. My appointment's at noon

25:19.474 --> 25:21.142
and I'll be home
right after that.

25:21.144 --> 25:22.710
<i>Your mother is worried sick.</i>

25:22.712 --> 25:24.178
<i>You have to come
pack your stuff.</i>

25:24.180 --> 25:26.181
Dad, this lawyer might
be able to help.

25:26.183 --> 25:28.782
Stop being
such a stubborn child.

25:28.784 --> 25:30.218
And get home now.

25:30.220 --> 25:32.119
Please, we have
to do something.

25:32.121 --> 25:34.888
This is honestly
our last chance.

25:34.890 --> 25:36.358
Come pack your stuff.

25:37.424 --> 25:38.259
I'm gonna throw it
all in the trash.

25:38.261 --> 25:41.397
Will you please just listen
to me for once?

26:04.187 --> 26:06.153
- Hello?
- <i>Is this Daniel Bae?</i>

26:06.155 --> 26:07.721
Yes, this is Daniel Bae.

26:07.723 --> 26:09.057
<i>My apologies, but Mr. Martinez</i>

26:09.059 --> 26:10.424
<i>needs to reschedule
our interview.</i>

26:10.426 --> 26:12.193
- Reschedule?
- <i>Tomorrow morning, 8:00.</i>

26:12.195 --> 26:14.695
Yeah! I think
I can make that work.

26:14.697 --> 26:16.029
<i>Okay. Wonderful.
Thank you so much.</i>

26:16.031 --> 26:17.266
Uh-huh. See you then.

26:21.338 --> 26:23.003
Yes!

26:30.079 --> 26:31.878
Hey.

26:31.880 --> 26:33.513
What was that all about?

26:33.515 --> 26:36.219
- Just parents being parents.
- Hmm.

26:39.088 --> 26:40.323
Loosened your tie.

26:40.857 --> 26:42.190
Yeah.

26:42.192 --> 26:44.661
Uh, my interview
got postponed to tomorrow.

26:45.561 --> 26:48.464
But back to love and science.

26:49.132 --> 26:52.400
So, this study

26:52.402 --> 26:56.037
had researchers put a bunch
of couples into a lab

26:56.039 --> 26:57.204
and had them ask each other

26:57.206 --> 26:59.340
a series
of intimate questions.

26:59.342 --> 27:00.842
Sounds ridiculous.

27:00.844 --> 27:02.144
At the end of the study,

27:02.146 --> 27:03.577
they had to stare
into each other's eyes

27:03.579 --> 27:07.382
for four minutes
without saying a word.

27:07.384 --> 27:08.817
So, you think
you're gonna make me

27:08.819 --> 27:11.754
fall in love by asking me
these questions?

27:13.123 --> 27:14.788
Okay, so there
are 36 questions.

27:14.790 --> 27:16.191
Okay, so we're doing this?

27:16.193 --> 27:17.759
But nobody's got time
for all that.

27:17.761 --> 27:19.762
So, how about I pick
ten randomly?

27:20.797 --> 27:23.700
Okay, question number one.

27:25.001 --> 27:26.299
What are the five
key ingredients

27:26.301 --> 27:28.470
to falling in love?

27:28.472 --> 27:30.808
This is so idiotic.
Um...

27:32.108 --> 27:33.240
Fine.

27:33.242 --> 27:35.242
Uh... Mutual self-interest

27:35.244 --> 27:38.247
and socioeconomic
compatibility.

27:39.382 --> 27:40.847
Okay.

27:40.849 --> 27:45.053
Well, my ingredients are
friendship and chemistry.

27:45.055 --> 27:46.453
Mmm. Of course they are.

27:46.455 --> 27:49.391
My last three are some
sort of moral compass...

27:49.393 --> 27:51.224
Common interests are a must.

27:51.226 --> 27:53.196
And let's see,

27:53.996 --> 27:55.195
the X factor.

27:55.197 --> 27:57.832
What in the world
is the X factor?

27:57.834 --> 27:59.603
Don't worry. We've got it.

28:02.239 --> 28:03.305
You know what...

28:03.307 --> 28:04.538
I hate to break this to you,

28:04.540 --> 28:06.074
but taking this little quiz

28:06.076 --> 28:09.877
isn't gonna make me change
my mind, Mr. Plaid Tie.

28:09.879 --> 28:11.746
Did you just call me Pad Thai?

28:11.748 --> 28:12.881
Plaid Tie.

28:12.883 --> 28:15.115
Because not only
is that completely racist,

28:15.117 --> 28:16.518
but also culturally
insensitive

28:16.520 --> 28:18.318
as my family is from Korea,
not Thailand.

28:18.320 --> 28:19.686
Well, that is not what I said,

28:19.688 --> 28:21.789
so you can stop waiting
for an apology.

28:21.791 --> 28:25.228
Oh, I'm waiting for something,
but not for an apology.

28:39.341 --> 28:40.875
Where are you going?

28:40.877 --> 28:42.779
I told you I have a meeting.

28:44.446 --> 28:47.150
Uh, we still have
27 minutes left.

28:47.684 --> 28:49.217
Mmm-hmm.

28:49.219 --> 28:51.255
So, you coming or what?

29:14.877 --> 29:17.578
So, where do you see yourself
in five years?

29:17.580 --> 29:19.380
Is that actually
one of the questions?

29:19.382 --> 29:21.149
I might be improvising.

29:21.151 --> 29:23.751
Well, I want to be
a data scientist.

29:23.753 --> 29:24.751
What's that?

29:24.753 --> 29:27.388
It's a scientist
who analyzes data.

29:27.390 --> 29:28.789
We take large amounts
of information

29:28.791 --> 29:31.926
and strategize on how
to apply it practically.

29:31.928 --> 29:32.993
Like how?

29:32.995 --> 29:34.862
Like traffic flow,

29:34.864 --> 29:37.198
four-day work weeks
for big companies,

29:37.200 --> 29:40.101
personal time
versus productivity.

29:40.103 --> 29:42.369
All that jazz. Come on.

29:42.371 --> 29:44.439
You're passionate
about it, though, right?

29:44.441 --> 29:45.906
Yeah, well,
I'm passionate

29:45.908 --> 29:47.409
about walking on the moon.

29:47.411 --> 29:48.843
But I can't live
off of passion

29:48.845 --> 29:52.278
any more than I can
live off of love.

29:52.280 --> 29:53.647
It's a long life to spend

29:53.649 --> 29:55.849
doing something
you're not really into.

29:55.851 --> 29:59.519
It's a long life
to spend chasing dreams.

29:59.521 --> 30:01.888
You should really kick it
with my dad sometime.

30:01.890 --> 30:05.092
Am I reminding you
of a 50-year-old Korean man?

30:05.094 --> 30:06.861
Without the accent.

30:06.863 --> 30:11.031
So, he's not crazy
about you pursuing poetry?

30:11.033 --> 30:13.634
Oh, no. I'm first-generation.

30:13.636 --> 30:14.836
And?

30:14.838 --> 30:16.770
It means it doesn't matter
what I want.

30:16.772 --> 30:21.041
According to my parents,
I'm meant to be a doctor.

30:21.043 --> 30:24.545
Oh. You know, at least when
you're a doctor making bank,

30:24.547 --> 30:26.079
you can thank them
for not letting you

30:26.081 --> 30:28.149
be a starving artist.

30:28.151 --> 30:31.521
It's hard to be passionate
when you're hungry.

30:32.321 --> 30:34.290
This is me.

30:46.903 --> 30:48.572
You're kidding.

30:51.107 --> 30:53.508
This is where my interview
was supposed to be.

30:53.510 --> 30:55.242
Come on. Honestly?

30:55.244 --> 30:57.112
I'm serious.
What are you doing here?

30:57.114 --> 30:58.913
Personal.

30:58.915 --> 31:00.381
Okay.

31:00.383 --> 31:02.549
But you gotta admit,

31:02.551 --> 31:05.419
this definitely
proves my point.

31:05.421 --> 31:07.321
Fate is real.

31:07.323 --> 31:09.589
Wait, I think
you mean coincidences,

31:09.591 --> 31:11.792
'cause they can happen
without meaning.

31:11.794 --> 31:12.896
Okay.

31:14.897 --> 31:16.329
Okay.

31:16.331 --> 31:17.632
I'll wait here for you

31:17.634 --> 31:18.801
and then we'll finish
the questions.

31:20.136 --> 31:23.807
Daniel, I should really
go home right after this.

31:24.941 --> 31:27.010
Today is a big day.

31:28.110 --> 31:31.314
So, I think this is where
we say goodbye.

31:36.185 --> 31:37.386
Um...

31:40.289 --> 31:42.722
Am I gonna see you again?

31:42.724 --> 31:45.660
The odds aren't in your favor.

31:45.662 --> 31:47.931
I'm guessing 1 in 8 million.

31:50.700 --> 31:52.532
I really think
I could have changed your mind

31:52.534 --> 31:53.936
if I had the whole day.

31:55.371 --> 31:58.541
Too bad you couldn't prove
your hypothesis.

32:00.777 --> 32:04.081
It was nice to save your life,
Natasha.

32:05.348 --> 32:08.383
Nice meeting you, Daniel.

32:08.385 --> 32:11.019
You know, good luck
with everything.

32:11.021 --> 32:14.087
Honestly, I hope
the interview goes well.

32:14.089 --> 32:15.458
Figure all that out.

32:16.459 --> 32:18.058
Thanks.

32:18.060 --> 32:19.495
Thanks again.

32:27.503 --> 32:29.905
You know,
I'm gonna prove my hypothesis!

32:31.007 --> 32:33.473
Love is real.

32:33.475 --> 32:35.978
This isn't the last time
I'm gonna see you.

32:37.579 --> 32:39.445
If I gotta hit up
all the boroughs,

32:39.447 --> 32:41.582
we're gonna see
each other again.

32:41.584 --> 32:43.553
You can't stop
what's meant to be.

32:49.759 --> 32:51.224
<i>The Theory of Multiverse</i>

32:51.226 --> 32:53.461
<i>was set forth originally
by Hugh Everett</i>

32:53.463 --> 32:55.363
<i>in quantum mechanics.</i>

32:55.365 --> 32:57.030
<i>It posited that every version</i>

32:57.032 --> 32:59.866
<i>of our past and future
histories exists,</i>

32:59.868 --> 33:01.937
<i>just in an alternate universe.</i>

33:04.139 --> 33:06.641
<i>This means that for every
choice you make,</i>

33:06.643 --> 33:08.910
<i>an infinite number
of universes exist</i>

33:08.912 --> 33:10.711
<i>where you made
a different choice.</i>

33:10.713 --> 33:14.048
<i>In this way,
we get to live multiple lives.</i>

33:14.050 --> 33:17.620
<i>I'm not quite sure which
universe I'm living in now.</i>

33:24.159 --> 33:26.429
Law offices
of Jeremy Martinez.

33:27.128 --> 33:29.195
Perfect. Okay, thank you.

33:30.398 --> 33:32.066
- Hi.
- Hi.

33:32.068 --> 33:33.634
Uh, I'm Natasha Kingsley.

33:33.636 --> 33:35.002
I was just about to call you.

33:35.004 --> 33:38.140
I am so sorry,
but I have some bad news.

33:39.642 --> 33:41.942
Mr. Martinez
was biking in to work

33:41.944 --> 33:43.644
when he got clipped by a car.

33:43.646 --> 33:45.278
But he was lucky.

33:45.280 --> 33:47.213
Just a few bruises.

33:47.215 --> 33:48.482
He'll be back around 4:30.

33:48.484 --> 33:49.951
Can you come back then?

33:49.953 --> 33:51.250
Law offices
of Jeremy Martinez.

33:51.252 --> 33:52.787
Of course. Of course.

33:52.789 --> 33:54.454
Um, I was supposed to help
my mother but I'll be here.

33:54.456 --> 33:56.289
Great. I need you
to fill these out.

33:56.291 --> 33:57.525
I already have my case files.

33:57.527 --> 33:58.792
You still need
to fill these out.

33:58.794 --> 34:00.394
You can take a seat
right over there.

34:00.396 --> 34:01.429
Okay.

34:01.431 --> 34:02.732
How can I help you?

34:12.175 --> 34:14.844
<i>"Have you ever
been convicted of a crime?"</i>

34:17.780 --> 34:19.783
Hey, get back here!

34:26.321 --> 34:27.920
<i>"Are you willing
to offer allegiance</i>

34:27.922 --> 34:29.755
<i>"to the United States
